Package: w-scan2
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A fork of the well-known w_scan project
 Channel scanning tool for DVB and ATSC channels
 w_scan2 scans for DVB-S/S2, DVB-T/T2, DVB-C and ATSC channels and creates a
 channels.conf, that can be used directly by the Linux Video Disc Recorder VDR.
 It is also possible to output channels in a format readable by the
 czap/tzap tools provided by linuxtv-dvb-zap, xine, totem or me-tv.
 .
 Unlike the scan utility in linuxtv-dvb-apps, there is no need to specify
 an initial transponder and w_scan2 automatically detects the DVB or ATSC
 card to be used.
